The paper deals with the sample complexity of learning with differential privacy, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses tools from information theory (cs.IT) and communication complexity (cs.CC) to derive its results. Additionally, the paper discusses the dimension of concept classes (cs.DS) and privacy in cryptography (cs.CR).
